laby, Leicestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William de Leicestershire Byrches was born in 1315, in Blaby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Lady William de Leicestershire Byrches. He died in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1315–":"1315–Surnud","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1343–1374":"1343–1374","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1315":"1315","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1374":"1374","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Blaby, Leicestershire, England":"Blaby, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"1315–":"1315–Kuollut","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1343–1374":"1343–1374","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1374":"1374","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Blaby, Leicestershire, England":"Blaby, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"1315–":"1315–Décédé","1320–Female":"1320–Décédée","1343–1374":"1343–1374","1315–Male":"1315–Décédé","1315":"1315","1343":"1343","1320":"1320","1374":"1374